social_posts.post_text: A few of my poster designs done in 2022. Thanks for all of the love and support this year ✨❤️

(Sorry for the reupload, the one I posted earlier had the wrong dates)

I am honored to share with you the upcoming tour poster I created for the WEST COAST @thediscobiscuits tour this summer. I have so many amazing memories seeing these guys with friends on the east coast and it’s an honor to be able to create art for an uncommon west coast tour from them now that I’ve lived out here for a while. The piece draws inspiration from the beautiful scenery driving to and through the West and the conglomeration of natural grooves, electronic and futuristic-spacey vibes tDB emanate. 
Hopefully will see some of you at the Los Angeles show! 
Side note: on this day 11 years ago, my Facebook status were lyrics to “Home Again”. Life is strange 👽✌🏻✨

I am beyond honored to share with you all my poster art for tonight’s @thecure show in San Diego 
The Cure’s “The Head on the Door” was one of the very first albums I ever owned 20 years ago, and to be able to contribute and create art for a band that has been a part of my life so long is very special to me. 
My poster art is an homage to the “Boys Don’t Cry” album art (you can see the cassette tape j card art on slide 2) and done in my style with some bright colors and sun shining on some palm trees for those Southern California vibes. 
Poster is available tonight at the show and at thecure.com and I will have some copies for sale in a few weeks as well. 
Thank you immensely to @collectionzz for having me ✨

Beauty is in the eyes of the Beholder 👁
Continuing on with my D&D monster illustration series is this Beholder I started on my iPad while on the airplane when I was traveling this past week. Which color variant do you all like the most? 
Comment below with what monster you’d like to see me do next.

“The fallen leaves tell a story, of how a Tarnished became Elden Lord…”

Finally beat Elden Ring a couple of days ago (anyone else here played?) and wanted to draw a piece inspired by the beautiful game as a practice piece for fun. Decided to draw my interpretation of the Elden Beast in an illustration style slightly inspired by retro RPG video games and my illustration style. Doing these types of pieces is a fun way to break away from my norm a bit and experiment and have fun.

My prints for @thecure are available now! You can buy both nights individually, or save a few dollars buying them as a set. These are signed by me and have the @collectionzz authentic sticker on the back. Available at www.GonzArt.com (link in bio)

Just realized I never shared this, but here is a shirt design I did for @gratefuldead . It is always an honor to create art for the band that brings us all together and love and admire so dearly. 10 years ago, 23 year old Nate would be flipping his lid and to be honest, I still am. This band has meant so much for so long, it’s just an innate part of who I/we are at this point. Anyways, before I ramble too much, for this piece I wanted to reflect on the beauty of the sunshine day dreams and the the strutting downtown at night vibes, all packaged into one beautiful, majestic, fluttering creature like the Dead are themselves. 
Thanks for looking and reading and hope you all have a lovely day ✨❤️

Poster art for @thehamiltonlivedc Days Between series of shows celebrating the life of Jerry Garcia. 5 nights of the Dead and Jerry inspired music with 4 great acts. Make sure to check it out if you’re in the area!

New single artwork for @jakobnowell new release “Time Traveler”, co-written by @timtimebomb and released on the one and only @epitaphrecords 
This was a fun one that really stretched myself a bit from my norm a bit. Jakob really liked an anime/retro future aesthetic that isn’t what I typically do, but thought I could maybe give it a go while still meshing in my style. Creating this retro-futuristic sci-fi android time traveler in death for love was a lot of fun and I’m really happy with how it came out. The simple obi-strip for the text really ties back the idea of the japanese influence as well. 
Thanks for looking and check out the song where ever you listen to music!

This Thursday, fear is the mind killer.

Denis Villeneuve’s Dune movies have re-engaged and re-energized pop culture interest and discussion of Frank Herbert’s brilliant story. We’re always excited to see artists, both new and old, create art for the epic story, and this week, @natemoonlife lets loose with a truly trippy take on Dune. Using an awesome symmetrical patterned approach, Nate’s art is like a precious stained glass window, offering a colorful peek into another world, and we totally dig every aspect of this piece. 

Stay tuned for more Dune art as the second film creeps closer!

Nate’s print will be available for purchase on Thursday (7/20) @ 12PM ET on our homepage, Bottleneckgallery.com!

"I must not fear.
Fear is the mind-killer.
Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration.
I will face my fear.
I will permit it to pass over me and through me.
And when it has gone past, I will turn the inner eye to see its path.
Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain."
It is an absolute honor and privilege to share with you all my officially licensed poster for DUNE @dunemovie with @bottleneckgallery 
Anyone who has followed me for a bit probably knows that Dune is an all time favorite book series of mine, and I have created several pieces, (prints, shirts, stickers etc), inspired by the amazing works of Frank Herbert. For this one, I wanted to really dive deep an offer a glimpse of the world of Dune, with references displayed in a psychedelic colorful and symmetrical way that feels like you perhaps just took a sip of the Water of Life. Paul stands upon his fathers legacy and stares down the powers and obstacles of his new home planet, all while dealing with a spiritual awakening and visions he can’t quite understand…yet. 
These limited edition prints are available starting now via Bottleneck Gallery in regular, metallic and foil editions. 
I’ll have some available on my site at some point as well for anyone looking for a signed one. 
Thank you for looking and “ bless the maker and his water. Bless the coming and going of him. May his passage cleanse the world. May he keep the world for his people”

God is in the rhythm ✨🚪✨ Have been wanting to make a new KGLW bootleg design for a while now since my Flying Microtonal Banana one back in 2019. I was sitting here last night listening to Nonagon Infinity, and this idea hit me like a big fig wasp and I had to make it real quick. So here is the Be Here Now x KGLW crossover no one asked for. First one I kept it to the traditional BHN colors, and the second slide I made it to match the style in the music video for “Robot Stop”
Thinking about printing some shirts or stickers or something. Help me out Weirdo Swarm, What color way and what do you all think I should do? Stickers? Shirts? Comment below with what you think and maybe even your favorite King Gizzard song.

I am honored to share this poster I designed for @maggierogers show tonight in Nashville, TN. I was given a brief to keep it simple, using bold, vintage style typography and some photos to focus on the “Twiggy-esque” large lash portraits in a fun composition. I am really happy with how it came out as it’s of course a little different from some of my more illustrative posters, but I love making retro/mid-century inspired designs regardless and using photos to manipulate a bit, and hope to do more like this in the future! 
I’ll have copies of these prints for sale in the upcoming weeks. Thanks for looking ✌🏻✨and thanks again @collectionzz

Everything under the sun is in tune, but the sun is eclipsed by the moon 🌞👁🌛
Stoked to share with you all the poster art for @govtmule Dark Side of the Mule show for tonight! As I’m sure some of you all know, Pink Floyd holds a dear space in my heart (I have ~50 Pink Floyd records) and has been a huge part of my life. When I first heard Govt Mule’s DSotM, it really tied together my love of Floyd and the amazing grooves of Govt Mule. For this poster, I wanted to do the same, using some inspiration from Pink Floyd songs and Storm Thorgerson’s surrealist style (who created most of their album art work) but distilling it through my vision and style and making it work for Govt Mule. 
Editions will be available at the show tonight, and mine should be available this weekend in both regular and rainbow foil.

I teamed up with the fine folks at @unioncraftbrewing to create this label design for them and @merriweatherpp 
Being from Baltimore originally, I’ve had many a Duckpins in the Merriweather lot (maybe too many during Tweezerfest 14) and to be able to contribute my art and be a part of this legacy is an honor. The art on the can features the infamous Frank Gehry pavilion and beautiful lawn with those summer vibes that seeing shows there emulates. This summer lager sounds like the perfect choice for sitting on that green lawn and watching your favorite bands with your friends and family while the sun sets. 
Thanks again @jonandtonic_79 and crew for having me. Always a hoot indeed ✨

It is an honor to share my poster art for tonight’s Queens of the Stone Age show at the @hartfordhealthcareamp 
I came up with a few concepts for this, but ultimately they approached me with a concept of a simple vintage matchbox design that can strike anytime, anywhere. Nero is known for instigating the Great Fire of Rome, so a matchbox seems fitting. I drew a lot of devil heads/faces for this while going back and digging through the QOTSA discography which I’ve been into since the release of SFTD, which was a lot of fun to do. It’s always fun to try something a little different than I typically do and stretch out a bit more. 
I’ll have a few artist copies available at some point in the future. Thanks for looking and enjoy the show for me if you go!

Poster art for tonight’s @umphreysmcgee show in Chattanooga, TN
When asked to do this poster, I was nudged to lean into more “rock n roll” vibes rather than a typical jam band poster. I presented two concepts, one and illustration in my “typical” style, and another one more rock and roll. For that, I leaned into that vintage pulp movie poster/paper back book cover style I’ve done in the past (like for TAB or DWG) to make this scene with some creepy crawlers from the area claiming a new home with a skull on some red planet with a portal to another realm/place in the background. 
I’ll have artist copies available soon, keep your eyes peeled on more info for those!

Poster art for international pop group @rbd_musica show last night at @mgmgrand in Las Vegas. 
Since these weren’t being screen printed, I decided to try out an 70’s-80’s airbrushing technique for this one with some soft shadows, highlights and color blends. It was fun to break out of my typical style and try something new stylistically.

Happy #BobbyDay to the one and only @bobweir ! ✨
@holymolymischief has arranged 76 artists to contribute to making sticker designs for a wonderful tribute series to celebrate the 76th birthday of Bob Weir. “Estimated Prophet” is one of my all time favorite Bobby songs, so when I got asked to contribute, I knew I had to do something inspired by that song, and make a classic style bumper sticker that would be perfect to slap on a back of a van and cruise down the PCH smelling the ocean breeze and feeling the sun and wind on your skin. The top design is the one I went with making (although I do enjoy the second one and maybe will print some of those if you all do, too) and I have some on www.themoonlife.com for you to slap on your bumper, your box where you keep your live tapes, or put it in a drawer never to be seen again like I do with most of my stickers. Thanks again Tony for having me part or this special #BW76 day ✨

My poster art for last nights @arcticmonkeys show in Belfast, Ireland. A lot of their poster art leans more into the abstract/geometric styles, so I thought it would be fun to give that a try in my own way and also kinda inspired by the Bauhaus design school styles. I set up some guidelines in Illustrator and started drawing shapes and letting them fall into place using those guides (see slide 2). Took that and brought into photoshop and had some fun with it to add the gradients and grain (kinda like airbrushing), using the shapes and color areas I blocked out in illustrator. The end result was something I couldn’t imagine, but allowing the process to guide me there led to the final design. It was very meditative to create in that aspect, just letting whatever comes flow through instead of having a predetermined concept for a final image. 
Anyways, it’s early and I am rambling now…I should have some copies in the future at some point as well ✨

My poster art for tonight’s @cahoneydrops gig in Pittsburgh. Gave it a very deco kinda border vibe to lend to the styles you see on some of the buildings in the city, too.  Had fun making this one and thanks to @consciousalliance for having me do this one ✨

Excited and honored to share my diptych for tonight and tomorrows @billystrings shows in Amsterdam. 
When coming up with concepts for this, my mind immediately went to the canals in Amsterdam and how I recently learned how many bikes and other “treasures” get pulled from the waters. Jumping off of this, I knew I could combine Billy’s love for fishing as well. What came from this was creating a slightly different style diptych than you typically see (setting it up so the prints stack vertically instead of side by side) to create the scene of the bridge and canals with a man fishing on the top, using all sort of warm colors with a splash of coolness, and down below going with an underwater scene of sorts with a whole other world to explore, with more cool colors and a splash of warmth. This was a really fun piece to create and I am really happy with how it came together in the end. 
•••

Another year to wrap up and put in the books. Thank you all for the support in 2023, it truly means the world to me to have been able to make a living doing what I love for over a decade. 2023 has brought on some seismic shifts in this industry that I think a lot of my peers have felt. Still, with everything I can’t help but smile looking back at some of the rad projects I got to work on this year. 
2024 is going to bring on a new change as I have started full time contracted graphic design work for a TTRPG/gaming company I am deeply passionate about and thrilled to be a part of. Here’s to a change, growth, new projects and lots of fun in 2024. 
Thanks all for being a part of this ride and see ya on the other side ✌🏻
